<paragraph blockId="41.[192,1440,961,1050]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,528,961,985]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Geographic distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[544,647,962,986]" captionStart="Figures 101–106" captionStartId="73.[192,288,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,192,1857]" captionTargetId="figure-47@73.[192,1440,192,1857]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="Figures 101–106. Species distribution maps. 101) Bembidion tillyardi. 102) B. townsendi. 103) B. urewerense. 104) B. waiho new species. 105) B. waimarama new species. 106) B. wanakense." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181796" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181796/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Fig. 104</figureCitation>
). South Island: 
<collectionCode box="[840,891,962,985]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">WD</collectionCode>
–Franz Josef, Waiho River. Hokitika. Karangarua River (between Highway 6 and Rough Creek). Poerua River (Highway 6 junction). Wanganui River (Highway 6 junction).
</paragraph>
